83rd OREGON LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY--2026 Regular Session
HOUSE AMENDMENTS TO
A-ENGROSSED HOUSE BILL 4061
By JOINT COMMITTEE ON WAYS AND MEANS
February 27
1 On page 1 of the printed A-engrossed bill, delete lines 4 through 6 and insert:
2 “SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expenditures, the limitation on
3 expenditures established by section 11 (1), chapter 616, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium
4 ending June 30, 2027, as the maximum limit for payment of expenses from lottery moneys
5 allocated from the Administrative Services Economic Development Fund to the Oregon
6 Business Development Department, for operations, is increased by $235,846, for implementa-
7 tion of section 2 of this 2026 Act.
8 “SECTION 1a. Notwithstanding any other law limiting expenditures, the limitation on
9 expenditures established by section 11 (2), chapter 616, Oregon Laws 2025, for the biennium
10 ending June 30, 2027, as the maximum limit for payment of expenses from lottery moneys
11 allocated from the Administrative Services Economic Development Fund to the Oregon
12 Business Development Department, for business, innovation and trade, is increased by
13 $950,000, for micro-enterprise tariff adjustment grants under section 2 of this 2026 Act.”.
14 On page 2, delete lines 25 through 45 and delete pages 3 and 4 and insert:
15 “SECTION 5. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public
16 peace, health and safety, an emergency is declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect
17 on its passage.”.
